7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to allow
8 municipal supervisory employees to organize and collectively bargain. This
9 bill also proposes to expand the definition of municipal public safety employee
10 to include support staff in public safety departments.
11 An act relating to the Vermont Municipal Labor Relations Act
12 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
13 Sec. 1. 21 V.S.A. § 1722 is amended to read:
14 § 1722. DEFINITIONS
15 As used in this chapter:
16 * * *
17 (12) “Municipal employee” means any employee of a municipal
18 employer, including a municipal school employee or a professional employee
19 as defined in subdivision 1502(11) of this title, except:
